ZCZC RE18
170650 UTC DEC 20
GREENLAND VIA SAUDANES
SYNOPSIS /2100 UTC.:
A HIGH 1025 HPA OVER NORTHEASTERN GREENLAND IS NOGENLUNDE STATIONARY.
COLD AIR WITH SCATTERED SNOW SHOWERS IS MOVING DOWN OVER THE NORTHEASTERN
WATERS. A STORM FORCE LOW 955 HPA SOUTH OF CAPE FAREWELL IS MOVING SLOWLY
TOWARDS EAST AND ASSOCIATED FRONT GIVES SNOW LOCALLY RAIN TO THE SOUTHERN
AND EASTERN WATERS. OVER THE WESTERN WATERS COLD NORTHERN FLOW WITH A FEW
SNOW SHOWERS.
